:INFO
Why Collect Rainwater?
A single 1-inch rainfall on a 1,000 square foot roof produces over 600 gallons \
of runoff. Most of that washes pollutants into storm drains. A rain barrel \
intercepts that water at the downspout and stores it for garden irrigation, \
reducing your water bill and the load on municipal drainage systems. In areas \
with summer water restrictions, a well-placed barrel can keep a kitchen garden \
productive through dry spells without drawing from the tap.

